featured_reviews.review_id:
Murdeshwar Temple is like a magical place on the western coast of India. Imagine a super tall, 20-story tower at the entrance, all covered in beautiful carvings and bright colors. It's like a huge, colorful castle!

Inside, there's a gigantic statue of Lord Shiva that looks out over the ocean. It's so huge that it's hard to believe. The temple is always kept super clean, and it feels really peaceful inside, like a special place for quiet thoughts.

The best part is that the temple is right next to the beach. So, you can watch the sunset over the sea while hearing the temple's soothing songs. It's like a dream!

I would tell all my friends to visit Murdeshwar Temple because it's a place where you can feel calm, see amazing art, and enjoy the beauty of the ocean all at once. It's like a magical adventure!

featured_reviews.review_id: The Murudeshwar Shiva statue stands tall as the third-largest Shiva statue in the world. This majestic and magnificent structure portrays Lord Shiva in a state of deep meditation. Set against the backdrop of the ocean, the statue creates a mesmerizing sight that captures the imagination. A visit to this iconic landmark is a must for anyone seeking spiritual solace and a chance to witness the grandeur of Indian mythology brought to life. Prepare to be awestruck by the sheer scale and beauty of this monumental tribute to Lord Shiva

featured_reviews.review_id: The Murudeshwar Temple is a sacred place of worship dedicated to Lord Shiva, the Hindu god of destruction and regeneration. The temple is renowned for its massive 123-foot tall. This impressive statue, which took over two years to build, is the second-highest Shiva statue in the world and can be seen from a distance. The placement of the statue allows it to gleam in the sunlight, making for a stunning sight in the morning hours.

This place has peace atmosphere with water rushing to the stones behind the temple hill. Behold one should walk more to get those feast on your eyes. The temple is open to visitors from 6 AM to 1 PM and from 3 PM to 8:15 PM. The temple is closed from 1 PM to 3 PM for lunch. Happy holidays...

featured_reviews.review_id:
The place is located on the beach one side it has large shiva idol, opposite to it a monumental tower and both sides are surrounded by the Arabian sea. The place is really good and gives you some very good vibes. We can actually buy a ticket and go in the lift into the tower and have the beautiful view,but as per the traditions, people say we shouldn't enter into those towers.

The maintenance at the temple for darshan was pathetic, no one to take care of public and there is no rush inside and they are stopping the line for more than half an hour. If there would have been proper maintenance and system, we could have completed our darshan in 15 mins, however it took 90 minutes for us which is really bad.

The parking is also a loot, they charge 30 rs and ask to enter inside, however the parking would be full inside and we have to go and park it in the beach which is actually free of cost. The police were very irresponsible and doesn't even take care of traffic. Due to one large bus we were struck in car for 1 hour and police were seeing the drama and enjoying it and had no sense of clearing the traffic and the people had to clear it at the end.

For more details and posts, please visit :

LETSTRAVELHYDERABAD on Instagram.
